yantra system steps
====================
dependencies installation
----------------------------
sudo apt install bison gawk gcc g++ make texinfo pkg-config grub-efi xorriso -y


1.take host system ubuntu 18.04.5

git clone https://github.com/yantraos/yantra-1.0.git

cd yantra-1.0

cd ybuild

./check.sh

need to install host system requirements follow below steps

2.linking /bin/sh to /bin/bash

sudo rm /bin/sh

sudo ln -s /bin/bash /bin/sh

3.installing Bison

sudo apt-get install bison -y

4.install with  gawk 

sudo apt-get install gawk -y

sudo rm /usr/bin/awk 

sudo ln -s /usr/bin/gawk /usr/bin/awk

5.gcc and g++
sudo apt install  gcc g++ make -y

6. install texinfo

sudo sudo apt-get install texinfo -y

7. install grub-efi

sudo apt-get grub-efi -y

8.install xorriso


sudo apt-gt install xorriso -y

9. install libssl-dev

sudo apt-get install libssl-dev -y

10.install pkg-config

sudo apt-get install pkg-config -y

11. install  yaps in hostsystem

cd yaps
sudo make install PREFIX=usr DESTDIR=/mnt/yantra/

12.version check

cd ybuild

13. ./check.sh

14.  ./01-toolchain.sh
15   ./02-system.sh
16.  ./03-makeiso.sh

